feat: version history with auto-snapshots and restore

Storage:
- Bumped DB_VERSION to 4, added 'versions' object store
- Indexes on noteid and timestamp for efficient queries
- Auto-prunes to 50 versions per note

Auto-Snapshot:
- Every save (manual or autosave) creates a version snapshot
- Stores title, body, tags, and timestamp
- Current state is saved before restoring an older version

Version History UI:
- Clock icon in note view toolbar opens version history modal
- Left panel: chronological version list with relative timestamps
- Right panel: full markdown preview of selected version
- Diff summary between consecutive versions (chars added/removed)
- Restore button overwrites current note with selected version
- Current state auto-saved before restore (safety net)

Functions added to notesDB.js:
- saveVersion(), getVersions(), getVersion()
- restoreVersion(), deleteVersions()

New file: src/VersionHistory.js
